<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="008" project="smart-todo-decoupling-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate `external-spa` to consume `sprk_todo` (rewrite `api/web-api-client.ts` + `EventsCalendar.tsx` + `SmartTodo.tsx`)</title>
    <phase>Phase 1: Dataverse Schema (audit-surfaced prerequisite)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4-6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>002, 007</dependencies>
    <blocks>004, 005</blocks>
    <tags>react, typescript, frontend, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Migrates an external-portal SPA from one entity contract to another. Modifies multiple `.ts`/`.tsx` files; FULL rigor.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>P1-W3</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Depends on task 007's DTO contract change.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Migrate `src/client/external-spa/` to consume the `sprk_todo` contract from task 007. Three files surface in the audit: `src/api/web-api-client.ts` (DTOs + queries with `sprk_todoflag` + `$select=...sprk_eventid,sprk_name,sprk_duedate,sprk_status,sprk_todoflag,...`); `src/components/EventsCalendar.tsx` (renders `event.sprk_todoflag` badge + creates events with `sprk_todoflag: false`); `src/components/SmartTodo.tsx` (the SPA's task list ŌĆö queries `sprk_event` filtered by `_sprk_projectid_value` AND `sprk_todoflag eq true`). Rewrite all three to consume `sprk_todo` records. Update mocks. Verify build + manual smoke test against the deployed BFF.
  </prompt>

  <role>Spaarke external-portal frontend developer.</role>

  <goal>External-spa uses `sprk_todo` throughout. `SmartTodo.tsx` queries `sprk_todos` filtered by the matching `sprk_regardingproject` resolver field. `EventsCalendar.tsx` separates event-rendering from todo-rendering (no more `event.sprk_todoflag` conditional). Build clean; manual smoke test against the BFF endpoints (after task 007 deploy) passes.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>The external-spa is the external-portal SPA hosted on Power Pages. The audit (task 001) found it directly queries `sprk_event` with the `todoflag=true` filter and renders todo badges based on `event.sprk_todoflag`. Decision (user, 2026-06-07): refactor/migrate ŌĆö this is important. Task 007 provides the new BFF DTO contract; this task consumes it.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/external-spa/src/api/web-api-client.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/external-spa/src/components/EventsCalendar.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/external-spa/src/components/SmartTodo.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/external-spa/src/mocks/ (mocks to update)</file>
      <file>projects/smart-todo-decoupling-r3/notes/external-access-contract-change.md (from task 007)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-29">Zero `sprk_todoflag` + `sprk_eventtodo` references in `src/client/external-spa/` after this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="OS-1">No compat shim.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Product portability: `external-spa` must NOT hardcode `https://spaarkedev1.crm.dynamics.com/` or any tenant-specific URL. All Dataverse endpoint construction goes through `config.ts` env vars / runtime config.</constraint>
    <constraint source="A-7 dep">Task 007's contract doc is the authoritative shape for the new DTOs.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/smart-todo-decoupling-r3/notes/external-access-contract-change.md</file>
      <file>projects/smart-todo-decoupling-r3/notes/eventtodo-reference-audit.md</file>
      <file>src/client/external-spa/README.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read task 007's contract doc + the three target files end-to-end. Map every legacy reference.</step>
    <step order="2">Update `api/web-api-client.ts`: replace the `sprk_event` query with a `sprk_todo` query (filter: matching regarding resolver field for the current project); update DTOs to the new shape (per task 007's contract doc).</step>
    <step order="3">Update `SmartTodo.tsx`: query for `sprk_todos` filtered by `_sprk_regardingproject_value eq '{projectId}'`; remove all `sprk_todoflag` references.</step>
    <step order="4">Update `EventsCalendar.tsx`: separate event-rendering from todo-rendering. If the calendar needs to show project to-dos alongside events, fetch from `sprk_todos` separately (two collections) instead of overloading `sprk_event` with a flag. Remove the `event.sprk_todoflag` conditional badge ŌĆö render a dedicated todo badge sourced from the new collection.</step>
    <step order="5">Update mocks in `src/mocks/` to reflect the new contract.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm run build` in `src/client/external-spa/` ŌĆö clean.</step>
    <step order="7">Manual smoke test against a deployed BFF (after task 007 completes): load the SPA, switch to a project, verify the SmartTodo list loads from `sprk_todos`, verify the calendar renders events without `sprk_todoflag` references in the DOM/Network tab.</step>
    <step order="8">Repo grep `src/client/external-spa/` for `sprk_todoflag`, `sprk_eventtodo`. Confirm zero hits.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md to Ō£ģ.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">`src/client/external-spa/src/api/web-api-client.ts` (refactored)</output>
    <output type="code">`src/client/external-spa/src/components/EventsCalendar.tsx` (refactored)</output>
    <output type="code">`src/client/external-spa/src/components/SmartTodo.tsx` (refactored)</output>
    <output type="code">`src/client/external-spa/src/mocks/*` (updated)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Build clean (`npm run build`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero `sprk_todoflag` + `sprk_eventtodo` references in `src/client/external-spa/`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SmartTodo list loads from `sprk_todos` (verified via browser Network tab or manual smoke test).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No hardcoded env URLs / tenant IDs in source code.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
